---
import EditorialPageLayout from "../layouts/EditorialPageLayout.astro";

const faqJsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "How do I log something in Memoato?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Open Quick Log and write what happened naturally. Memoato saves the raw note first, then processes useful categories and details in the background.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "What happens to my original note?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "The original raw entry is preserved. Derived events and labels stay linked to it so corrections do not duplicate the source log.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "What are categories?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Categories are views and metrics such as Weight, Pull ups, Football, or Notes. They help organize facts extracted from raw entries and can also be logged directly.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can I edit or delete my history?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. You can edit and delete entries from category history. You can also export your data or delete your account from Profile.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "What privacy options are available?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Memoato supports cloud sync, encrypted cloud, and local-only storage. Change the mode under Profile and Privacy.",
      },
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      name: "Can I connect Codex or Claude?",
      acceptedAnswer: {
        "@type": "Answer",
        text: "Yes. Create a scoped API key in Profile and connect to the hosted Memoato MCP endpoint.",
      },
    },
  ],
};
const faqJsonLdString = JSON.stringify(faqJsonLd);
---

<EditorialPageLayout
  title="Help · memoato"
  description="How to capture, organize, review, and protect your memories in Memoato."
  canonicalPath="/help"
  eyebrow="Help & FAQ"
  heading="Start with what happened."
  deck="You do not need to design a tracking system before using Memoato. One honest sentence is enough to begin."
  accent="sage"
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={faqJsonLdString} />

  <p>
    Open <a href="https://app.memoato.com">Quick Log</a>, write the thing in your own words, and submit it. Memoato saves
    the original note immediately. Useful structure can appear afterward without making you wait at capture time.
  </p>

  <h2>What can I write?</h2>
  <p>Anything that might matter later. Short is fine. Messy is fine. A few examples:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>Low energy, skipped gym, walked 20 minutes after lunch</code></li>
    <li><code>89.8 kg</code></li>
    <li><code>Pull ups 2 2 3</code></li>
    <li><code>Bought car battery, 59 EUR, two year warranty</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What happens to the raw note?</h2>
  <p>
    It stays intact. Memoato may derive categories, values, timestamps, and context from it, but the original source is
    preserved. Derived entries remain linked to the raw log so later corrections update the meaning without duplicating
    what you wrote.
  </p>

  <h2>What are categories?</h2>
  <p>
    Categories are useful views and metrics — Weight, Pull ups, Football, Energy, Notes, and anything personal to you.
    They are no longer the only way to begin a log. You can write naturally and let Memoato match existing categories,
    or open a category directly when you already know exactly what you want to add.
  </p>

  <h2>How does the Timeline work?</h2>
  <p>
    Timeline gives you a day-by-day view of what happened. It groups related entries, keeps notes readable, and lets you
    move backward through your history without opening every category individually.
  </p>

  <h2>Can I edit, delete, or reorder things?</h2>
  <p>
    Yes. Category history supports editing and deletion. Home categories can be reordered from Edit mode. Your profile
    also includes data export and account deletion controls.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy modes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cloud sync</strong> — the simplest multi-device experience.</li>
    <li><strong>Encrypted cloud</strong> — category titles and notes are encrypted on your device before saving.</li>
    <li><strong>Local-only</strong> — data stays in the browser on that device.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Open <strong>Profile → Privacy</strong> to review or switch modes. Read the full <a href="/privacy">privacy policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Can Codex or Claude log for me?</h2>
  <p>
    Yes. Create a scoped, revocable API key under <strong>Profile → API keys</strong>, then connect the hosted Memoato
    MCP. Agents can read category metadata and create labeled raw entries without receiving your account password.
  </p>

  <h2>Still stuck?</h2>
  <p>
    Email <a href="mailto:hello@memoato.com">hello@memoato.com</a> or open an issue in the
    <a href="https://github.com/hrvojepavlinovic/memoato-app/issues" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a>.
  </p>
</EditorialPageLayout>
